         <div type="apparatus"/>
         <div type="translation" resp="part:argr">
 	         <p rend="stanza" n="1"><!-- The gist seems to be that a most superior ascetic (yatīśvaraḥ) called Matimaha, whose feet were worshipped by a variety of beings (perhaps one could read something like surasurāridaityanareśvarārccitapadaḥ, “whose feet were worshipped gods, demons inimical to gods and kings”), and whose mind was unwavering in the face of torment (could one read pīḍananiścalamatiḥ?), having passed away and attained liberation (padam acalaṃ gatvā), is superior over all (jayati). It is in his honour, and presumably on the same lordly mountain where he once meditated (śailarāje ’smin), that Rudravarman has erected this inscription. --></p>
         </div>
